# Implementation Plan - Navigation & New Views

## Goal
Implement functionality to switch between "Dashboard", "Ship Tracking", "Truck Tracking", and "History" screens using the sidebar menu. Create the basic layout and functionality for these new screens (starting with History).

## Proposed Changes

### 1. HTML Structure ([index.html](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/index.html))
- **Add View Containers**: Create hidden `div` containers for each new view alongside the existing `#dashboard-view`.
  - `#ship-tracking-view`
  - `#truck-tracking-view`
  - `#history-view`
- **History View Layout**: Add a table for past records and a search filter.

### 2. Styling ([style.css](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/style.css))
- **Utility Classes**: Ensure `.hidden` class works correctly for hiding views.
- **Table Styles**: Reuse existing table styles for the History view.

### 3. Logic ([app.js](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/app.js))
- **Navigation Handler**:
  - Add event listeners to sidebar links (`.nav-item`).
  - Implement a function `switchView(viewId)` to hide all views and show the selected one.
  - Update the `active` class on the sidebar menu.
- **History Logic**:
  - Implement rendering for the history table (filtering completed batches).

## Verification Plan
- Click each menu item (Dashboard, Ship, Truck, History) and verify the main content area updates accordingly.
- Verify that the "History" view displays data (we can mock some completed data vs active data).
